Reasoning: The paper deals with the axiomatic characterization of different types of complexity, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as it deals with the study of information and its properties, including Kolmogorov complexity. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as it deals with the study of the resources required to solve computational problems, which is related to complexity. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely category as it deals with the design and analysis of algorithms, which is relevant to the study of complexity. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also possible as the paper deals with axiomatic systems. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but still possible as the study of complexity is relevant to cryptography and security.
